Title : Marc Kestecher
Text : '''Marc Kestecher''' is a [[Sports commentator|play-by-play announcer]] [[radio]] [[Sportscaster|sports]] and [[News presenter|news anchor]]. He was raised in [[Guilderland, New York]] and began his play-by-play work for the [[Albany Patroons]] following 3 years of studies at [[Syracuse University]]. <ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesunion.com/tuplus-sports/article/Kestecher-waited-patiently-to-finally-land-dream-8379505.php|title=Kestecher waited patiently to finally land dream job|last=Dougherty|first=Pete|date=2016-07-15|website=Times Union|access-date=2019-06-14}}</ref> Kestecher later took studio positions at [[WKNR]] in [[Cleveland]] and [[WPTR (AM)]] and [[WROW]] in [[Albany, New York]] where he provided score updates and hosted talk programming. <ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://awfulannouncing.com/2016/espn-radio-names-marc-kestecher-as-its-voice-of-the-nba.html|title=ESPN Radio names Marc Kestecher as its Voice of the NBA|last=Fang|first=Ken|date=2016-07-13|website=Awful Announcing|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-14}}</ref> Kestecher joined [[ESPN Radio]] in 1999, first hosting [[ESPN Radio SportsCenter]] and ESPN Radio's studio coverage of major sporting events. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://espnpressroom.com/us/bios/kestecher_marc/|title=Marc Kestecher|website=ESPN Press Room U.S.|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-14}}</ref>

He was named as the lead play-by-play announcer for the [[NBA on ESPN Radio]] in 2016, replacing [[Kevin Calabro]] who opted to return to the Pacific Northwest to call play-by-play for the [[Portland Trail Blazers]]. In this role he calls the [[NBA playoffs]] and [[NBA Finals]] with [[Hubie Brown]]. <ref name=":1" /> Kestecher also does play-by-play for college football games and [[Football Sunday on ESPN Radio]]. <ref name=":0" /> In addition to his radio work, he also does play-by-play for ESPN's coverage of the [[NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Tournament]] and select [[NBA on ESPN]] games when the main staff has other commitments<ref name=":0" />, and college football games for Group of 5 conference games on [[ESPNU]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://awfulannouncing.com/schedules/your-2018-college-football-week-10-announcing-schedule.html|title=Your 2018 college football Week 10 announcing schedule|date=2018-11-01|website=Awful Announcing|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-14}}</ref>. 


